<html xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:w="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>CloudPro Test Cases</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif; }
  h1 { text-align: center; color: #333; }
  h2 { color: #444; border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc; padding-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 30px; }
  table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid #000; padding: 10px; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
  th { background-color: #d9e1f2; font-weight: bold; }
  .pass { color: #008000; font-weight: bold; }
  .fail { color: #FF0000; font-weight: bold; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>CloudPro - Manual Test Cases Execution Report</h1>
<p><strong>Date:</strong> June 4, 2026</p>
<p><strong>Tester:</strong> QA Team (AI)</p>
<p><strong>Overall Status:</strong> All core functionalities are working as expected.</p>

<h2>1. Authentication Module</h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Test Case ID</th>
    <th>Test Scenario</th>
    <th>Steps to Execute</th>
    <th>Expected Result</th>
    <th>Status</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-AUTH-01</td>
    <td>Successful Registration</td>
    <td>1. Navigate to /register.<br>2. Enter valid Name, Email, and Password.<br>3. Click "Sign Up".</td>
    <td>User is registered successfully, backend logs the user, and redirects to Login page.</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-AUTH-02</td>
    <td>Registration with Existing Email</td>
    <td>1. Navigate to /register.<br>2. Enter an email that is already registered.<br>3. Click "Sign Up".</td>
    <td>System displays an error: "User already exists".</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-AUTH-03</td>
    <td>Successful Login & OTP</td>
    <td>1. Navigate to /login.<br>2. Enter valid Email and Password.<br>3. Click "Login".</td>
    <td>System verifies credentials and sends a 6-digit OTP to the user's email. UI routes to OTP entry.</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-AUTH-04</td>
    <td>Verify OTP</td>
    <td>1. Enter the correct OTP sent to email.<br>2. Click "Verify".</td>
    <td>User is authenticated, JWT token is stored, and user is redirected to Dashboard.</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-AUTH-05</td>
    <td>Invalid Credentials</td>
    <td>1. Enter valid email but incorrect password.<br>2. Click "Login".</td>
    <td>System displays "Invalid email or password" error.</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h2>2. File Management & Storage</h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Test Case ID</th>
    <th>Test Scenario</th>
    <th>Steps to Execute</th>
    <th>Expected Result</th>
    <th>Status</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-FILE-01</td>
    <td>Upload Valid File</td>
    <td>1. On Dashboard, click "Upload".<br>2. Select a valid image or PDF.<br>3. Click Upload.</td>
    <td>File uploads successfully, appears in the file grid, and storage usage ring increases.</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-FILE-02</td>
    <td>Upload Exceeding Limit</td>
    <td>1. Ensure user is a Standard User (15 GB limit).<br>2. Attempt to upload a file that exceeds the remaining storage capacity.</td>
    <td>Upload is blocked by the backend, error message alerts the user of insufficient storage.</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-FILE-03</td>
    <td>File Categorization</td>
    <td>1. Upload a .jpg file and a .pdf file.<br>2. Check the category tags on the dashboard.</td>
    <td>.jpg is auto-tagged as "Media", .pdf is auto-tagged as "Document".</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-FILE-04</td>
    <td>File Preview</td>
    <td>1. Click on an uploaded image or video file.</td>
    <td>A modal opens displaying the file preview securely via a pre-signed S3 URL.</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>TC-FILE-05</td>
    <td>Delete File (Soft Delete)</td>
    <td>1. Click the trash icon on a file.<br>2. Confirm deletion.</td>
    <td>File disappears from main grid and is moved to the "Trash" state in the database.</td>
    <td class="pass">PASS</td>
  </tr>
</table>

